events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron hurt, Hawks beat Lakers 99-94 for 8th straight win

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 23 of his 29 points in the first half and fell just short of a triple-double to lead the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers over the Sacramento Kings 129-105 on Saturday night.

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas and Dillon Brooks scored 19 points each, Valanciunas added 15 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Golden State Warriors 111-103 on Saturday night, splitting the two-game set between the teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas, Brooks lead Grizzlies past Warriors, 111-103

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points and a season-high 15 assists, leading the Milwaukee Bucks to a 120-113 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Spurs 120-113 for season-best 6th straight win

headlines.description: — Paul George had 21 points and 10 assists, Kawhi Leonard added 17 points and the Los Angeles Clippers emerged from two inconsistent weeks with a 125-98 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Leonard lead Clippers' 125-98 rout of Hornets
